The paper proposes a machine learning model for predicting photovoltaic power generation based on weather data. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The model uses a Long-Term Recurrent Convolutional Network (LRCN) architecture, which is a type of neural network commonly used for spatio-temporal data. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), which are sub-categories related to neural networks and software development, respectively. Finally, the paper focuses on the application of the model to energy forecasting, which could also place it under the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category.
